tip.text: Pho is huge and delightful, as are the dry noodle dishes. Rice dishes are average. Get some rice paper rolls (if you can finish the main dishes) The owner is really nice as well, which is a bonus.
Get the lobster Benedict if you're feeling hungry!

tip.text: Visited for the first time in 5 years after moving away from the East Coast area. Food remains affordable and great, despite the shorthanded kitchen and wait staff. Certainly worth the wait, though.

tip.text: Try visiting at off-peak hours to miss the local mob that descends upon this venerable establishment. Dishes in general are great and fresh but make sure you get the prawns if you're on a budget.
Get here early to buy your Sintra tickets...or face queues like this. The early bird really gets the worm.

tip.text: Service is a little tight - lipped but still cordial. You can't go wrong with Octopus a Galega and the Black Pork main. Paella for 2 has decent value though slightly salty. I'd recommend this place.
